This paper proposes a new model for regulation to achieve AI safety, which falls under the category of AI (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of AI models in commercial drones, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper addresses the risk of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the costs and benefits of the proposed approach, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
